.TH "of_slim_get_device" 9 "of_slim_get_device" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_slim_get_device \- get handle to a device using dt node.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct slim_device *" of_slim_get_device
.BI "(struct slim_controller *ctrl "  ","
.BI "struct device_node *np "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctrl" 12
Controller on which this device will be added/queried
.IP "np" 12
node pointer to device
.SH "RETURN"
pointer to a device if it has already reported. Creates a new
device and returns pointer to it if the device has not yet enumerated.
